%h1
  Creating gemsets
%p
  Gemsets must be created before being used.
  Creating new gemsets for the current ruby can be done as follows:

%pre.code
  :preserve
    $ rvm 1.9.2-head
    $ rvm gemset create albinochipmunk
    Gemset 'albinochipmunk' created.
%p
  Multiple gemsets may be created in the same command.

%pre.code
  :preserve
    $ rvm 1.9.2-head
    $ rvm gemset create albinochipmunk redsquirrel
    Gemset 'albinochipmunk' created.
    Gemset 'redsquirrel' created.

%p
  Alternatively, if you prefer the short hand syntax
  offered by rvm use, you can use the --create option
  like so:

= sh_cmd "rvm use 1.9.2-head@albinochipmunk --create"
